IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: PATIENT CENTERED HEALTHCARE SYSTEM ENHANCING THE LIVES OF INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES BY PROVIDING ACCESS TO AFFORDABLE COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH AND WELLNESS SERVICES IN MONTGOMERY AND THE SURROUNDING AREAS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: HEALTH SERVICES, INC. (HSI) IS A MEDICAL HOME PROVIDING ACCESS TO AFFORDABLE PRIMARY, PREVENTIVE AND WELLNESS SERVICES DISTINGUISHED BY COMPASSION, QUALITY, INTEGRITY AND RESPECT.
IRS990.Desc: HSI SERVED APPROXIMATELY 37,000 PATIENTS ACCOUNTING FOR APPROXIMATELY 117,000 VISITS DURING THE YEAR. THE VISITS COVERED A BROAD RANGE OF SERVICES INCLUDING GENERAL WELLNESS AND PRIMARY CARE, PEDIATRICS, DENTISTRY, OPTOMETRY, OB/GYN AND FAMILY PLANNING AND FAMILY CARE; COUNSELING AND PSYCHIATRY FOR VARIOUS TREATMENT AND DISORDERS IN CHILDREN AND ADULTS; MILITARY AND VETERAN RESOURCES, SPECIALTY REFERRALS, ENROLLMENT SERVICES AND THE WOMEN, INFANTS & CHILDREN (WIC) PROGRAM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC) AND SIMILAR PROVISIONS OF ALABAMA LAW AND IS CLASSIFIED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AS AN ORGANIZATION OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. AS OF AND FOR THE YEAR ENDED JANUARY 31, 2023, THE ORGANIZATION HAD NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT QUALIFY FOR RECOGNITION OR DISCLOSURE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND NO INTEREST AND PENALTIES RELATED TO INCOME TAXES.
CEO HAS A WRITTEN CONTRACT THAT WAS APPROVED BY THE BOARD.
EMPLOYED PROVIDERS (MEDICAL DOCTORS, PHYSICIAN ASSISTANTS, AND NURSE PRACTITIONERS) RECEIVED INCENTIVES BASED UPON TOTAL ENCOUNTERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONTROLLER, CFO, AND CEO REVIEW SUPPORT DOCUMENTS AND TAX RETURN.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IT IS MONITORED BY THE CORPORATE COMPLIANCE OFFICER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS UTILIZE AN INDEPENDENT NATIONAL LEGAL FIRM OF THE ORGANIZATION'S ASSOCIATION TO DETERMINE APPROPRIATE CEO COMPENSATION. OTHER KEY EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY USING PUBLISHED MATERIALS AND LOCAL COMPARABILITY DATA.
